Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{3} (or use a #garlic press{}). Pop half the garlic
into a #medium bowl{} with the @lemon & herb seasoning{1%sachet} and the
@olive oil{2%tbsp} for the marinade. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and mix
together.

Add the @skin-on British chicken breasts{2} to the bowl and mix to coat well.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g}. Stir-fry until golden,
~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Once golden, set aside for now.

Clean the frying pan, then pop back on medium-high heat (no oil). Lay the chicken
into the pan, skin-side down. Fry until the skin is golden, ~{5-6%minutes}, then
turn and cook for ~{1%minute} on the other side.

Meanwhile, chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Halve and
peel the @red onions{2}(quartered), then quarter each half.

Pop the veg onto a #large baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with salt and
pepper, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast the potatoes and onions on the middle shelf until
golden, ~{30-40%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Once seared, transfer the chicken to another #baking tray{}, skin-side up, then
roast on the top shelf until cooked, ~{18-25%minutes}.

When the chicken is cooked, transfer to a #chopping board{} to rest for a couple
of mins loosely covered in #foil{}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While everything roasts, in a #small bowl{}, combine the remaining garlic,
@tomato puree{30%g}, @mango chutney{40%g} and @water{2%tbsp} for the sauce. Set
aside.

Once the veg has roasted, add the sticky sauce to the tray and mix together until
well coated.

Lay the @chopped kale{100%g} on top of the sticky veg, drizzle with a little oil
and season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: Remove any tough stalks from the kale.

Return the tray to your oven and bake on the middle shelf until the kale is
crispy, ~{7-8%minutes}.

When everything's ready, cut the chicken widthways into 2cm thick slices.

Mix the bacon, potatoes, onions and kale together in the tray and share between
your plates.

Top with the lemon and herb chicken.

Enjoy!